ss1.p:
It was the custom of the Jews in like manner to anoint themselves with oil, as a means of refreshing or invigorating their bodies (
 Deuteronomy 28:40; 
 Ruth 3:3; 
2 Samuel 14:2; 
 Psalms 104:15, etc.). The 
Hellenes had similar customs. This custom is continued among the Arabs to the present day.

The High Priest and the king are each sometimes called "the anointed" (
 Leviticus 4:3-5, 
4:16; 
6:20; 
 Psalm 132:10). Prophets were also anointed (
1 Kings 19:16; 
1 Chronicles 16:22; 
 Psalm 105:15).

The New Testament records that oil was applied to the sick, and also to wounds 
 Mark 6:13; 
 James 5:14).

The bodies of the dead were sometimes anointed (
 Mark 14:8; 
 Luke 23:56).
